<div class="page-hero"><p class="page-eyebrow">Model Guide</p><h1 class="page-h1">Veo Camera Prompt Generator</h1>
<p class="page-intro">Shot Lab automatically formats your inputs to match Veo's preferred prompt style. Select Veo in the model tabs and generate.</p></div>
<div class="sect"><h2 class="sect-h">Generate a Veo prompt</h2><div class="mini-gen" id="mg-veo">Loading generator...</div><script src="../../data/models.js"></script><script src="../../js/mini-generator.js"></script><script>initMiniGenerator("mg-veo",null,"","");</script></div>
<div class="sect"><h2 class="sect-h">About Veo prompt formatting</h2><div class="info-card"><p>Veo by Google DeepMind responds well to 'A cinematic shot of...' framing and detailed environmental description. Write camera movement as part of the narrative using 'the camera performs a...' phrasing.</p><p style="margin-top:8px"><strong>Default ratio:</strong> 16:9</p></div></div>
<div class="sect"><h2 class="sect-h">Tips for Veo prompts</h2><div class="body-copy"><ul><li>Open with 'A cinematic shot of...' for best results.</li><li>Describe camera movement mid-narrative: 'the camera performs a slow dolly push-in...'</li><li>Include environment context: weather, time of day, location type.</li><li>End with style, lighting, and aspect ratio in parentheses.</li><li>Veo handles lighting descriptions with high fidelity.</li></ul></div></div>
<div class="sect"><h2 class="sect-h">Recommended camera moves</h2><div class="rel-strip"><span class="rel-pill">Slow Dolly In</span><span class="rel-pill">Crane Up</span><span class="rel-pill">Orbit Shot</span><span class="rel-pill">Drone Fly-Over</span><span class="rel-pill">Rack Focus</span><span class="rel-pill">POV Walk</span></div></div>
<div class="sect"><h2 class="sect-h">Example prompts</h2><div class="prompt-list"><div class="prompt-item"><div class="pt-label">Landscape</div><div class="pt-text">A cinematic shot of a vast canyon at golden hour. The camera performs a drone fly-over from altitude, slowly descending to reveal a lone figure on the rim. Cinematic nature documentary. Golden-hour light, long shadows. Slow majestic pacing. (16:9)</div><button class="pt-copy">Copy</button></div><div class="prompt-item"><div class="pt-label">Action</div><div class="pt-text">A cinematic shot of a warrior launching into a battle charge. The camera performs a fast dolly rush-in. Epic fantasy action style. Harsh backlight, debris. Fast pacing. (16:9)</div><button class="pt-copy">Copy</button></div><div class="prompt-item"><div class="pt-label">Drama</div><div class="pt-text">A cinematic shot of two friends sitting in silence on a rooftop at night. The camera performs a slow orbit. Quiet indie drama style. Warm city light below, cold night sky. Steady pacing. (16:9)</div><button class="pt-copy">Copy</button></div></div></div>
<div class="sect"><h2 class="sect-h">FAQ</h2><div class="faq"><details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-q">Best Veo prompt structure?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></summary><div class="faq-a">Subject/scene context → camera movement → style → lighting → aspect ratio. Use 'the camera performs a...' for movement.</div></details><details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-q">Realism or stylised content?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></summary><div class="faq-a">Veo is strongest at photorealistic and cinematic content. For anime, be very explicit about the style.</div></details><details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-q">Does Veo support audio?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></summary><div class="faq-a">Veo 2+ can generate ambient audio alongside video. Append audio descriptions at the end of your prompt.</div></details><details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-q">What camera moves does Veo interpret reliably?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></summary><div class="faq-a">Dolly moves, Crane Up/Down, Orbit, and aerial shots. Use the 'the camera performs a...' framing.</div></details></div>
